	<dl>
	<dt>There's no point. Within the next 5 ...</dt>
	<dd><p>There's no point. Within the next 5 years society as we know it will have broken down as world oil demand outstrips supply. And before the protests start, we aren't waiting for the oil to actually run out; all it will take is for the markets to worry and the price to rise above a certain point - and stay there. Once this happens, and petrol stations start to close down, people will start to panic. Government crackdowns will be next. Wait and see. Our doom is upon us.</p>
	<small>
	written 29th Apr 2005 <!--  | <a href="../email/1602">Email this
    to a friend</a> | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=1602">abusive?</a> -->
	</small>
	</dd>
	</dl>

